<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title><%= title %></title>
  <style>
    body { 
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif; 
      text-align: center; 
      background-color: #f4f4f4; 
      margin: 0; 
      padding: 0; 
    }
    h1 { margin-top: 20px; color: #333; }

    /* Array container */
    #arrayContainer { 
      margin: 20px auto; 
      display: flex; 
      justify-content: center; 
      gap: 10px; 
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      max-width: 800px;
      padding: 10px;
      background: #fff;
      border: 2px solid #333;
      border-radius: 10px;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
    }
    .array-item { 
      width: 60px; 
      height: 60px; 
      background: #4CAF50; 
      color: white; 
      display: flex; 
      align-items: center; 
      justify-content: center; 
      font-weight: bold;
      border-radius: 8px;
      transition: transform 0.3s ease, background 0.3s ease;
    }
    .array-item.highlight { 
      background: #FF9800; 
      transform: scale(1.1); 
    }

    /* Form */
    .form-container {
      margin: 20px auto;
    }
    input, select, button {
      padding: 10px; 
      margin: 5px;
      border-radius: 5px;
    }
    button {
      cursor: pointer;
      background: #2196F3;
      color: white;
      border: none;
    }

    /* Content */
    .content {
      text-align: left;
      margin: 40px auto;
      max-width: 900px;
      background: #fff;
      padding: 20px;
      border-radius: 10px;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
    }
    pre {
      background: #222; 
      color: #eee; 
      padding: 10px; 
      border-radius: 5px; 
      overflow-x: auto;
    }
    table {
      width: 100%; 
      border-collapse: collapse; 
      margin: 15px 0;
    }
    th, td {
      border: 1px solid #333; 
      padding: 8px; 
      text-align: center;
    }
    th { background: #4CAF50; color: white; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Array Visualizer</h1>

  <!-- Form -->
  <div class="form-container">
    <form action="/dsa/array" method="POST">
      <input type="number" name="index" placeholder="Index" required>
      <input type="text" name="value" placeholder="Value">
      <select name="operation">
        <option value="insert">Insert</option>
        <option value="update">Update</option>
        <option value="delete">Delete</option>
        <option value="search">Search</option>
      </select>
      <button type="submit">Perform</button>
    </form>
  </div>

  <!-- Array Display -->
  <div id="arrayContainer"></div>

  <a href="/">Back to Home</a>

  <!-- Content Section -->
  <div class="content">
    <h2>What is an Array?</h2>
    <p>
      An <b>array</b> is a linear data structure that stores elements at <b>contiguous memory locations</b>. 
      It allows random access using indexes, making it one of the most widely used structures.
    </p>

    <h2>Code Snippets</h2>
    <h3>Java</h3>
    <pre>
int arr[] = new int[5];
arr[0] = 10;
arr[1] = 20;
System.out.println(arr[1]); // 20
    </pre>

    <h3>Python</h3>
    <pre>
arr = [10, 20, 30]
arr[1] = 25
print(arr[1])  # 25
    </pre>

    <h3>C</h3>
    <pre>
int arr[5];
arr[0] = 10;
arr[1] = 20;
printf("%d", arr[1]); // 20
    </pre>

    <h3>JavaScript</h3>
    <pre>
let arr = [10, 20, 30];
arr[1] = 25;
console.log(arr[1]); // 25
    </pre>

    <h2>Time Complexity</h2>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Operation</th><th>Time Complexity</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Access</td><td>O(1)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Update</td><td>O(1)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Insert (end)</td><td>O(1)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Insert (middle)</td><td>O(n)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Delete</td><td>O(n)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Search</td><td>O(n)</td></tr>
    </table>

    <h2>Advantages</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Fast random access using indexes</li>
      <li>Easy to implement and use</li>
      <li>Efficient for fixed-size collections</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Disadvantages</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Fixed size (cannot grow dynamically)</li>
      <li>Insertion/Deletion in middle is costly</li>
      <li>Wastes memory if not fully utilized</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

